text.tspan: Clinical trials by type of intervention

Annual number of completed clinical trials registered globally in the
ClinicalTrials.gov
database by the type of
treatment they investigate. Treatments can include drugs, biologicals, devices, radiation or surgical treatment,
but also behavioral interventions, diagnostic tests, dietary supplement or a combination of multiple of these.
Note: Some studies include multiple types of interventions, and are counted multiple times (once for each intervention type). ClinicalTrials.gov
